Jive CEO Elisa Steele to Join Panel at G100 Women’s Leadership Acceleration Spring 2017 Forum
June 8, 2017Topics
Jive News
 


linkedin


twitter


google+


Facebook


Email



 
A critical component of leadership is making good decisions—the uncertain environment and velocity of business change create constant pressure for timely and effective decision-making. Jive CEO Elisa Steele will address this topic during a panel at the exclusive G100 Women’s Leadership Acceleration Spring 2017 Forum on Thursday, June 15, from 1:15 – 2:00 p.m. at the Parc 55 Hotel in San Francisco.
Elisa will be joined onstage by Helen Wesley, CFO of ENMAX, and Maggie Wilderotter, the former CEO of Frontier Communications and panel moderator. The session will dig into how to understand hidden biases that influence decisions, the role of judgement when one doesn’t have all the information but needs to make a call, and how to harness the power of an organization to improve the decision-making process.
Elisa Steele to join G100 panel on how to improve decision makingThe Spring 2017 Forum, to be held June 14-16, 2017, is part of the G100 Women’s Leadership Acceleration Program, a development experience for women executives who aspire to C-suite positions. The 10-month program enhances C-suite readiness through a powerful combination of skills enrichment, network building and career management strategies that will demonstrably elevate the executive’s value to the organization.
Find out More About the G100 Women’s Leadership Acceleration Spring 2017 Forum 


